{"video_id": "bLUgYC-iRho", "title": "096  Srila Prabhupada's is parampara understanding of philosophy", "speaker": "HDG Srila Prabhupada", "youtube_url": "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=bLUgYC-iRho", "duration": 236, "segments": [{"start": 0.0, "end": 3.0, "text": " Subtitles by the Amara.org community"}, {"start": 7.0, "end": 9.0, "text": " What is the condition of people in general?"}, {"start": 11.0, "end": 14.0, "text": " There are so many subject matters for discussing"}, {"start": 14.0, "end": 16.0, "text": " but they don't discuss about Krishna"}, {"start": 16.0, "end": 19.0, "text": " because they are blind to self-realization."}, {"start": 19.0, "end": 21.0, "text": " Why? Because they are attached to"}, {"start": 25.0, "end": 28.0, "text": " happy home, family life."}, {"start": 28.0, "end": 35.0, "text": " And their time in family life"}, {"start": 35.0, "end": 40.0, "text": " is spent away both day and night"}, {"start": 40.0, "end": 44.0, "text": " in some activities which have no spiritual benefit."}, {"start": 52.0, "end": 55.0, "text": " The lifetime, Prabhupada translates"}, {"start": 58.0, "end": 65.0, "text": " this verse"}, {"start": 65.0, "end": 69.0, "text": " as the lifetime of such an envious householder."}, {"start": 69.0, "end": 72.0, "text": " He doesn't say just householder."}, {"start": 72.0, "end": 74.0, "text": " So when we were translating"}, {"start": 74.0, "end": 77.0, "text": " or getting it translated this English to Kannada"}, {"start": 77.0, "end": 79.0, "text": " the Bhagavatam"}, {"start": 79.0, "end": 82.0, "text": " one translator objected to this."}, {"start": 82.0, "end": 85.0, "text": " He says where in the verse"}, {"start": 85.0, "end": 87.0, "text": " Sanskrit verse it is said"}, {"start": 87.0, "end": 89.0, "text": " envious householder."}, {"start": 92.0, "end": 94.0, "text": " He doesn't say envious householder."}, {"start": 94.0, "end": 97.0, "text": " The word envy is not used in Sanskrit."}, {"start": 97.0, "end": 100.0, "text": " Why is Prabhupada telling envious householder?"}, {"start": 100.0, "end": 102.0, "text": " So there is a mistake in the translation"}, {"start": 102.0, "end": 104.0, "text": " or there is some problem here."}, {"start": 105.0, "end": 108.0, "text": " Actually, Prabhupada translates"}, {"start": 109.0, "end": 112.0, "text": " not just literally always."}, {"start": 113.0, "end": 115.0, "text": " Prabhupada is giving"}, {"start": 115.0, "end": 118.0, "text": " the parampara understanding."}, {"start": 120.0, "end": 122.0, "text": " The parampara understanding."}, {"start": 122.0, "end": 124.0, "text": " You should not forget that."}, {"start": 125.0, "end": 128.0, "text": " Prabhupada is not just taking the Sanskrit"}, {"start": 128.0, "end": 130.0, "text": " and writing the English."}, {"start": 130.0, "end": 132.0, "text": " No."}, {"start": 132.0, "end": 135.0, "text": " He is giving the parampara understanding."}, {"start": 137.0, "end": 139.0, "text": " The Acharyas explain"}, {"start": 139.0, "end": 143.0, "text": " how a householder who is blind to self-realization"}, {"start": 143.0, "end": 146.0, "text": " who is attached to family life"}, {"start": 146.0, "end": 148.0, "text": " is an envious person."}, {"start": 151.0, "end": 153.0, "text": " Elsewhere"}, {"start": 153.0, "end": 155.0, "text": " Prabhupada says"}, {"start": 155.0, "end": 157.0, "text": " what is the difference between a"}, {"start": 157.0, "end": 160.0, "text": " grahamedhi and a grahasta?"}, {"start": 162.0, "end": 165.0, "text": " Grahamedhi"}, {"start": 165.0, "end": 168.0, "text": " is explained as"}, {"start": 168.0, "end": 170.0, "text": " an envious householder."}, {"start": 173.0, "end": 175.0, "text": " Envious householder."}, {"start": 175.0, "end": 178.0, "text": " Because such a person"}, {"start": 178.0, "end": 181.0, "text": " is busy always"}, {"start": 183.0, "end": 186.0, "text": " with his limited self-interest."}, {"start": 189.0, "end": 190.0, "text": " What is the self,"}, {"start": 190.0, "end": 192.0, "text": " conception of the self?"}, {"start": 192.0, "end": 194.0, "text": " I am the body"}, {"start": 195.0, "end": 198.0, "text": " and my bodily connections are"}, {"start": 198.0, "end": 200.0, "text": " mine."}, {"start": 200.0, "end": 202.0, "text": " Aham ameti."}, {"start": 202.0, "end": 204.0, "text": " This is the"}, {"start": 204.0, "end": 206.0, "text": " conception of the"}, {"start": 206.0, "end": 208.0, "text": " householder"}, {"start": 208.0, "end": 210.0, "text": " who is blind to self-realization"}, {"start": 210.0, "end": 212.0, "text": " who is materially attached"}, {"start": 212.0, "end": 213.0, "text": " to family life."}, {"start": 213.0, "end": 215.0, "text": " Therefore such a person is described"}, {"start": 215.0, "end": 217.0, "text": " as an envious householder."}, {"start": 219.0, "end": 221.0, "text": " So this translation says"}, {"start": 221.0, "end": 223.0, "text": " the lifetime of such an envious householder"}, {"start": 223.0, "end": 225.0, "text": " is passed at night"}, {"start": 225.0, "end": 227.0, "text": " either in sleeping or in sex indulgence."}, {"start": 227.0, "end": 229.0, "text": " Bhagavatam is very strong."}, {"start": 232.0, "end": 233.0, "text": " I would like to talk about"}, {"start": 233.0, "end": 234.0, "text": " this chapter and"}, {"start": 234.0, "end": 235.0, "text": " the thoughts about"}, {"start": 235.0, "end": 236.0, "text": " the Maha Sri Ram."}, {"start": 236.0, "end": 238.0, "text": " We understand that"}, {"start": 238.0, "end": 239.0, "text": " the Maha Sri Ram is not"}, {"start": 239.0, "end": 240.0, "text": " like the rest of the world."}, {"start": 240.0, "end": 242.0, "text": " As in the context of my"}, {"start": 242.0, "end": 243.0, "text": " life,"}, {"start": 243.0, "end": 244.0, "text": " I was in this world"}, {"start": 244.0, "end": 245.0, "text": " for only a few"}, {"start": 245.0, "end": 246.0, "text": " years."}, {"start": 246.0, "end": 247.0, "text": " Whatever you"}, {"start": 247.0, "end": 248.0, "text": " feel about"}, {"start": 248.0, "end": 249.0, "text": " this world,"}, {"start": 249.0, "end": 250.0, "text": " or any other"}, {"start": 250.0, "end": 251.0, "text": " world,"}, {"start": 251.0, "end": 252.0, "text": " this world"}, {"start": 252.0, "end": 253.0, "text": " has more"}, {"start": 253.0, "end": 254.0, "text": " and more"}, {"start": 254.0, "end": 255.0, "text": " beings."}, {"start": 255.0, "end": 256.0, "text": " But"}, {"start": 256.0, "end": 257.0, "text": " on the other hand,"}, {"start": 257.0, "end": 258.0, "text": " I am in this world"}, {"start": 258.0, "end": 259.0, "text": " for life."}, {"start": 259.0, "end": 260.0, "text": " That is the"}, {"start": 260.0, "end": 261.0, "text": " world that I am in."}]}